parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ejection of a spark plug can cause engine damage, fuel leaks, and potentially lead to a fire, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Loud popping or banging noise
loss of power
engine stalling
fuel leaks
and smoke or fire from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the camshaft position sensor can cause the engine to stall or lose power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine stalling
loss of power
difficulty starting the engine
and warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft position sensor can cause the engine to stall or lose power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine stalling
loss of power
difficulty starting the engine
and warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leaks can cause fires, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Fuel smell
fuel leaks
and smoke or fire from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine stalling
loss of power
and difficulty restarting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates abnormally
the tire makes a popping sound
the tire blows out
the tread separates from the tire
the tire has uneven wear
and the tire makes noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The spare tire cable bracket failure can cause the spare tire to detach from the vehicle, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The spare tire cable bracket fractures and detaches
causing the spare tire to drop from the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to honor recalls and reimburse consumers can lead to continued use of defective tires, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Consumers experience difficulties in getting reimbursed for defective tires
and manufacturers fail to honor recalls or provide replacement tires in a timely manner.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brake pedal to sink to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sinks to the floor
the vehicle does not stop or slows down abnormally
brake fluid leaks from the master cylinder reservoir.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate or jerk when braking, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates or jerks when braking
the brake pedal pulsates
the brake rotors are excessively worn or warped.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper slide bracket can cause uneven brake activation, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side when braking
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pads wear unevenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the brake fluid lines can cause brake fluid leaks, leading to a loss of braking power, which can cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake fluid leaks from the brake lines
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle does not stop or slows down abnormally.
